. As suggested by the process, the regular icosahedron is also known as <b>=
snub octahedron</b>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEKappraff1991[httpsbooksgoog=
lecombooksidtz76s0ZGFiQCpgPA475_475]_8-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
