<p>The regular icosahedron can be unfolded into 43,380 different <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Net_(geometry)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Net (geometry)">nets</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEDennisMcNairWoolfK=
auffman2018[httpsbooksgooglecombooksid4hVeDwAAQBAJpgPA169_169]_9-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_icosahedron=
